# Village Public Toilet Jieliuzi Proprietary Closed-source Open Source License
Version 1.0, April 2026 | For Entertainment Only | Not Legally Valid

## Preamble
This License governs the use, modification, distribution, squatting, loitering, smoking, chatting, napping, and “hanging out without doing anything” of the Village Public Toilet (VPT) and its associated facilities (stalls, urinals, sinks, mirrors, tissue boxes, footrests, ventilation fans, and random graffiti). It is a hybrid proprietary–closed‑source–open source joke license exclusively for Jieliuzi (street loafers) and casual users.

By entering, using, or loitering within 3 meters of the VPT, you accept all terms below. If you disagree, you must leave immediately, wash your hands, and never come back until you understand humor.

## 1. Definitions
- VPT: Village Public Toilet, the physical and spiritual home of local Jieliuzi.
- Jieliuzi: A person who spends 80% of their day in or around the VPT, does no real work, and treats the toilet as a private club, lounge, office, or second home.
- Proprietary Part: The toilet structure, plumbing, lighting, lock mechanisms, and official village signs. Closed‑source; no reverse‑engineering, digging, or breaking allowed.
- Open‑Source Part: Air, seating experience, chatting rights, loitering permissions, and the right to leave harmless graffiti (no insults to the village chief).
- User: Anyone who uses the VPT for its intended purpose OR for Jieliuzi‑style loitering.
- Derivative Work: A modified usage pattern, such as bringing a chair, playing music, hosting a small meeting, or napping in a stall.

## 2. Proprietary Closed‑Source Terms
- You may NOT copy, clone, rebuild, or mass‑produce the VPT in another village without written permission from the Village Committee and the Head Jieliuzi.
- You may NOT reverse‑engineer the plumbing, pick locks, vandalize stalls, or steal toilet paper.
- You may NOT repackage the VPT as a “luxury private toilet” and charge money. This is a public good, not your business.
- Any violation results in temporary banishment from the VPT and mandatory cleaning duty for 3 days.

## 3. Open‑Source Permissions
You are free to:
- Use the VPT for its original sanitary purpose, no fee, no registration.
- Loiter, lean against walls, squat on footrests, chat, smoke (gently), and exchange village gossip.
- Modify your personal behavior (e.g., bring a cup of tea, play phone videos, take a light nap).
- Distribute stories about the VPT to other villages, as long as you credit “The Original VPT of [Your Village]”.
- Contribute improvements: wiping sinks, picking up trash, or telling others to keep it clean.

## 4. Conditions for Open‑Source Use
- You must keep quiet during peak hours (morning rush, lunch break, evening cleanup).
- You must not block the door or occupy a stall for more than 30 minutes without a valid reason (Jieliuzi loitering is a valid reason).
- You must not write insulting or political graffiti; harmless memes and jokes are allowed.
- If you modify your usage (e.g., host a small chat group), you must allow other Jieliuzi to join freely — no exclusive clubs.

## 5. Dual‑License Exception for Jieliuzi
- Jieliuzi Mode: Automatic open‑source loitering rights, free seating, priority access to the best‑ventilated stall.
- Normal User Mode: Standard public toilet rules, no loitering priority.
- You may switch modes at any time, but you cannot abuse Jieliuzi Mode to bully others.

## 6. Disclaimer of Warranty
THE VPT IS PROVIDED “AS IS”, WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF CLEANLINESS, DRYNESS, ODOR‑LESSNESS, TISSUE AVAILABILITY, OR COMFORT.
IN NO EVENT SHALL THE VILLAGE COMMITTEE, HEAD JIELIUZI, OR CLEANING STAFF BE LIABLE FOR ANY DAMAGE, INCONVENIENCE, EMBARRASSMENT, OR LOST LOITERING TIME ARISING FROM USE OF THE VPT.

## 7. Termination
- This License terminates automatically if you vandalize, pollute, or turn the VPT into a garbage dump.
- Upon termination, you must surrender all Jieliuzi privileges and may not loiter within 10 meters of the VPT for one week.
- If you correct your behavior, you may apply for reinstatement to the Head Jieliuzi.

## 8. Miscellaneous
- This License is a joke. Do not take it seriously.
- If a lawyer reads this, they should smile and go use the toilet.
- The Head Jieliuzi has final interpretation rights — because they spend the most time here.

